{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hj12AorrQUPfydU6LfvVPt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * step1.cu -- K_Step1 SPH density summation + strain-rate tensor kernel.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Per-particle computation:\n     5→ *   density_sum += m_j * (h^2 - |r_ij|^2)^3   for all neighbors j within h\n     6→ *   density_i = max(1.0, poly6_coeff * density_sum)\n     7→ *\n     8→ * For GRANULAR particles only, also computes the symmetric strain-rate tensor D\n     9→ * using the SPH velocity gradient with spiky gradient weighting:\n    10→ *   D_ab = 0.5 * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (dv_a * gradW_b + dv_b * gradW_a)\n    11→ * Then: gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D) = sqrt(2 * (Dxx^2 + Dyy^2 + Dzz^2 + 2*(Dxy^2 + Dxz^2 + Dyz^2)))\n    12→ *\n    13→ * Operates on SORTED particle arrays (after hash + sort + reorder).\n    14→ * Uses 27-cell neighbor iteration with grid cell_start/cell_end tables.\n    15→ * Self-interaction IS included for density (j==i NOT skipped).\n    16→ * Self-interaction is skipped for strain-rate (j==i skipped).\n    17→ * Per-particle mass m_j supports multi-material and mass splitting.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * Ported from SPHSimLib/K_SimpleSPH_Step1.inl + K_SPH_Kernels_poly6.inl.\n    20→ * Neighbor iteration ported from SPHSimLib/K_UniformGrid_Utils.inl.\n    21→ *\n    22→ * Constant memory (c_grid, c_sim, c_precalc) declared in common.cuh.\n    23→ */\n    24→\n    25→#include \"common.cuh\"\n    26→\n    27→extern \"C\" __global__\n    28→void K_Step1(\n    29→    uint            numParticles,\n    30→    const float4*   __restrict__ position,      // sorted positions\n    31→    const float4*   __restrict__ velocity,      // sorted velocities (for strain-rate)\n    32→    const float*    __restrict__ mass,           // sorted per-particle mass\n    33→    const float*    __restrict__ density_in,     // sorted density from previous step (for strain-rate m_j/rho_j weighting; NULL on first frame)\n    34→    const uint*     __restrict__ packed_info,    // sorted packed_info (for behavior class check)\n    35→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_start,     // grid cell start indices\n    36→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_end,       // grid cell end indices\n    37→    float*          __restrict__ density_out,    // output: density per particle\n    38→    float*          __restrict__ shear_rate_out  // output: gamma_dot per particle (0 for non-GRANULAR)\n    39→) {\n    40→    uint index_i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n    41→    if (index_i >= numParticles) return;\n    42→\n    43→    // Read position of particle i\n    44→    float4 pos4_i = position[index_i];\n    45→    float3 pos_i = make_float3(pos4_i.x, pos4_i.y, pos4_i.z);\n    46→\n    47→    float h    = c_sim.smoothing_length;\n    48→    float h_sq = c_sim.smoothing_length_sq;\n    49→\n    50→    // Check if this particle is GRANULAR\n    51→    uint pi_i = __ldg(&packed_info[index_i]);\n    52→    int behavior_i = GET_BEHAVIOR(pi_i);\n    53→    bool is_granular = (behavior_i == GRANULAR);\n    54→\n    55→    // Read velocity for strain-rate (only used if GRANULAR, but cheap to read)\n    56→    float3 vel_i;\n    57→    if (is_granular) {\n    58→        float4 vel4_i = velocity[index_i];\n    59→        vel_i = make_float3(vel4_i.x, vel4_i.y, vel4_i.z);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    // Density accumulator (variable part of Poly6 kernel)\n    63→    float sum_density = 0.0f;\n    64→\n    65→    // Strain-rate tensor accumulators (6 symmetric components)\n    66→    // D_xx, D_yy, D_zz, D_xy, D_xz, D_yz\n    67→    float Dxx = 0.0f, Dyy = 0.0f, Dzz = 0.0f;\n    68→    float Dxy = 0.0f, Dxz = 0.0f, Dyz = 0.0f;\n    69→\n    70→    // Grid cell of particle i\n    71→    int3 cell_i = make_int3(\n    72→        (int)((pos_i.x - c_grid.grid_min.x) * c_grid.grid_delta.x),\n    73→        (int)((pos_i.y - c_grid.grid_min.y) * c_grid.grid_delta.y),\n    74→        (int)((pos_i.z - c_grid.grid_min.z) * c_grid.grid_delta.z)\n    75→    );\n    76→    // Clamp to valid range\n    77→    cell_i.x = max(0, min(cell_i.x, c_grid.grid_res.x - 1));\n    78→    cell_i.y = max(0, min(cell_i.y, c_grid.grid_res.y - 1));\n    79→    cell_i.z = max(0, min(cell_i.z, c_grid.grid_res.z - 1));\n    80→\n    81→    int rx = c_grid.grid_res.x;\n    82→    int ry = c_grid.grid_res.y;\n    83→    int rz = c_grid.grid_res.z;\n    84→\n    85→    // Iterate 27 neighbor cells\n    86→    for (int dz = -1; dz <= 1; dz++) {\n    87→        int cz = cell_i.z + dz;\n    88→        if (cz < 0 || cz >= rz) continue;\n    89→        for (int dy = -1; dy <= 1; dy++) {\n    90→            int cy = cell_i.y + dy;\n    91→            if (cy < 0 || cy >= ry) continue;\n    92→            for (int dx = -1; dx <= 1; dx++) {\n    93→                int cx = cell_i.x + dx;\n    94→                if (cx < 0 || cx >= rx) continue;\n    95→\n    96→                uint hash = (uint)(cz * ry * rx + cy * rx + cx);\n    97→                uint start = cell_start[hash];\n    98→\n    99→                // Empty cell sentinel\n   100→                if (start == 0xFFFFFFFFu) continue;\n   101→                uint end_idx = cell_end[hash];\n   102→\n   103→                for (uint index_j = start; index_j < end_idx; index_j++) {\n   104→                    float4 pos4_j = __ldg(&position[index_j]);\n   105→                    float3 r = make_float3(\n   106→                        pos_i.x - pos4_j.x,\n   107→                        pos_i.y - pos4_j.y,\n   108→                        pos_i.z - pos4_j.z\n   109→                    );\n   110→                    float r_sq = r.x * r.x + r.y * r.y + r.z * r.z;\n   111→\n   112→                    if (r_sq <= h_sq) {\n   113→                        // --- Density: self-interaction included ---\n   114→                        float diff = h_sq - r_sq;\n   115→                        float m_j = __ldg(&mass[index_j]);\n   116→                        sum_density += m_j * diff * diff * diff;\n   117→\n   118→                        // --- Strain-rate: skip self, GRANULAR only ---\n   119→                        if (is_granular && index_j != index_i && r_sq > 1e-12f) {\n   120→                            float rlen = sqrtf(r_sq);\n   121→\n   122→                            // Spiky gradient: gradW = spiky_grad_coeff * (h - r)^2 * (r/|r|)\n   123→                            // spiky_grad_coeff is negative (-45/(pi*h^6))\n   124→                            // We need the actual gradient vector pointing from j to i\n   125→                            float h_r = h - rlen;\n   126→                            float inv_rlen = 1.0f / rlen;\n   127→                            // gradW = spiky_grad_coeff * (h-r)^2 * r_hat\n   128→                            // where r_hat = r/|r| points from j to i\n   129→                            float grad_scalar = c_precalc.spiky_grad_coeff * h_r * h_r * inv_rlen;\n   130→                            float gWx = grad_scalar * r.x;\n   131→                            float gWy = grad_scalar * r.y;\n   132→                            float gWz = grad_scalar * r.z;\n   133→\n   134→                            // dv = v_i - v_j\n   135→                            float4 vel4_j = __ldg(&velocity[index_j]);\n   136→                            float dvx = vel_i.x - vel4_j.x;\n   137→                            float dvy = vel_i.y - vel4_j.y;\n   138→                            float dvz = vel_i.z - vel4_j.z;\n   139→\n   140→                            // m_j / rho_j weighting\n   141→                            float rho_j = (density_in != 0) ? __ldg(&density_in[index_j]) : 1000.0f;\n   142→                            float weight = m_j / fmaxf(rho_j, 1.0f);\n   143→\n   144→                            // Accumulate velocity gradient tensor L_ab = sum (m_j/rho_j) * dv_a * gradW_b\n   145→                            // D_ab = 0.5 * (L_ab + L_ba)\n   146→                            // Since we compute D directly:\n   147→                            //   D_xx += weight * dv_x * gW_x\n   148→                            //   D_yy += weight * dv_y * gW_y\n   149→                            //   D_zz += weight * dv_z * gW_z\n   150→                            //   D_xy += 0.5 * weight * (dv_x * gW_y + dv_y * gW_x)\n   151→                            //   D_xz += 0.5 * weight * (dv_x * gW_z + dv_z * gW_x)\n   152→                            //   D_yz += 0.5 * weight * (dv_y * gW_z + dv_z * gW_y)\n   153→                            Dxx += weight * dvx * gWx;\n   154→                            Dyy += weight * dvy * gWy;\n   155→                            Dzz += weight * dvz * gWz;\n   156→                            Dxy += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWy + dvy * gWx);\n   157→                            Dxz += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWz + dvz * gWx);\n   158→                            Dyz += 0.5f * weight * (dvy * gWz + dvz * gWy);\n   159→                        }\n   160→                    }\n   161→                }\n   162→            }\n   163→        }\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    // --- PostCalc: density ---\n   167→    float density = c_precalc.poly6_coeff * sum_density;\n   168→    density_out[index_i] = fmaxf(density, 1.0f);\n   169→\n   170→    // --- PostCalc: strain-rate magnitude (gamma_dot) ---\n   171→    if (is_granular) {\n   172→        // gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D)\n   173→        //           = sqrt(2 * (Dxx^2 + Dyy^2 + Dzz^2 + 2*(Dxy^2 + Dxz^2 + Dyz^2)))\n   174→        float D_sq = Dxx * Dxx + Dyy * Dyy + Dzz * Dzz\n   175→                   + 2.0f * (Dxy * Dxy + Dxz * Dxz + Dyz * Dyz);\n   176→        float gamma_dot = sqrtf(fmaxf(2.0f * D_sq, 0.0f));\n   177→        shear_rate_out[index_i] = gamma_dot;\n   178→    } else {\n   179→        shear_rate_out[index_i] = 0.0f;\n   180→    }\n   181→}\n   182→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01347Ms3n2ztvJGmYvu6iFwH","session_id":"2b25de12-98cf-4fd9-9de1-d55f6bd80115","uuid":"ab23a9f6-9261-4ff9-bf5d-38d6f1732343"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01347Ms3n2ztvJGmYvu6iFwH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: Step2 Kernel & mu(I) Rheology Implementation\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the `/c/WORK/gpusphsim` codebase and identified all mu(I) rheology implementations and related components. Here are the key findings:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Step2 Kernel Implementation**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step2.cu`\n\nThe Step2 kernel implements:\n- Tait EOS pressure computation (behavior-specific: FLUID, GRANULAR, GAS)\n- Pressure force accumulation via spiky gradient\n- **mu(I) viscosity for GRANULAR particles** (primary rheology implementation)\n- Constant viscosity for FLUID/GAS particles\n- XSPH correction (FLUID only)\n\n**Key Algorithm Flow (lines 1-406):**\n\n1. **Per-Material Tait EOS** (lines 63-81):\n   - FLUID: `p = max(k * (pow(rho/rho0, 7) - 1), -0.5*k)` — allows small tensile pressure\n   - GRANULAR: `p = max(k * (pow(rho/rho0, 7) - 1), 0)` — non-negative pressure only\n   - GAS: `p = k * max(rho - rho0, 0)` — linear EOS (gamma=1)\n\n2. **Strain Rate Magnitude Computation** (lines 207-268):\n   - For GRANULAR particles: First neighbor pass to compute `gamma_dot_i`\n   - Sum: `gamma_dot_sq_sum += (m_j/rho_j) * |v_ij|^2 * (h-r)^2/r`\n   - Apply gradient normalization: `gamma_dot_i = sqrt(45/(pi*h^6) * gamma_dot_sq_sum)`\n\n3. **mu(I) Rheology** (lines 120-130):\n   ```cuda\n   I_number = gamma_dot * spacing / sqrt(p_eff / rho)\n   mu_I = mu_s + (mu_2 - mu_s) / (1 + I0 / max(I, 1e-8))\n   eta_i = min(mu_max, mu0 + mu_I * p_eff / (gamma_dot + 1e-6))\n   ```\n\n4. **Pair-wise Viscosity for GRANULAR-GRANULAR** (lines 326-345):\n   - Compute `gamma_dot_j` directly from relative velocity\n   - **Harmonic mean**: `eta_ij = 2*eta_i*eta_j / (eta_i + eta_j + 1e-8)`\n   - Apply full coefficient baked in: `visc_force = eta_ij * 45/(pi*h^6) * m_j * (h-r) / rho_j * (v_j - v_i)`\n\n5. **Constant Viscosity for Mixed Pairs** (lines 346-359):\n   - GRANULAR-nonGRANULAR: Uses constant `mu0` with full coefficient\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Behavior Classes Definition**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` (lines 22-27)\n\n```cuda\nenum BehaviorClass {\n    FLUID   = 0,\n    GRANULAR = 1,\n    GAS     = 2,\n    STATIC  = 3\n};\n```\n\n**Python Reference:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/materials.py` (lines 72-75)\n```python\nFLUID = 0\nGRANULAR = 1\nGAS = 2\nSTATIC = 3\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **mu(I) Parameters Structure**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step2.cu` (lines 40-51)\n\n```cuda\nstruct GranularParams {\n    float mu_s;               // static friction (0.36)\n    float mu_2;               // dynamic friction (0.70)\n    float I0;                 // inertial reference (0.3)\n    float mu_max;             // viscosity clamp (10000 Pa*s)\n    float particle_spacing;   // d (0.02)\n    float mu0;                // base viscosity (3.5)\n    float xsph_epsilon;       // XSPH blending (0.5)\n    float _pad0;              // padding\n};\n```\n\n**Default Values in Python:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/step2.py` (lines 42-48)\n```python\nDEFAULT_MU_S = np.float32(0.36)\nDEFAULT_MU_2 = np.float32(0.70)\nDEFAULT_I0 = np.float32(0.3)\nDEFAULT_MU_MAX = np.float32(10000.0)\nDEFAULT_PARTICLE_SPACING = np.float32(0.02)\nDEFAULT_MU0 = np.float32(3.5)\nDEFAULT_XSPH_EPSILON = np.float32(0.5)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Materials Properties Definition**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` (lines 34-51)\n\n```cuda\nstruct MaterialProps {\n    float rest_density;          // kg/m^3\n    float eos_stiffness;         // Tait EOS k\n    float eos_gamma;             // EOS exponent (7 or 1)\n    float base_viscosity;        // Pa*s\n    float friction_coeff;        // mu_s (stored but not used in Step2)\n    float cohesion;              // (placeholder)\n    float buoyancy_extra;        // (placeholder)\n    float thermal_conductivity;  // (placeholder)\n    float heat_capacity;         // (placeholder)\n    float temp_melt;             // (placeholder)\n    float temp_boil;             // (placeholder)\n    float temp_ignite;           // (placeholder)\n    int   behavior_class;        // BehaviorClass enum\n    float color_r, color_g, color_b;\n};\n```\n\n**Material ID Constants:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/materials.py` (lines 137-152)\n```python\nDEAD = 0, STONE = 1, SAND = 2, DIRT = 3, GRAVEL = 4\nWATER = 5, OIL = 6, LAVA = 7, ACID = 8\nWOOD = 9, METAL = 10, ICE = 11\nSTEAM = 12, SMOKE = 13, FIRE = 14, GUNPOWDER = 15\n```\n\n**Material Behavior Mapping:**\n- GRANULAR: SAND (2), DIRT (3), GRAVEL (4), GUNPOWDER (15)\n- FLUID: WATER (5), OIL (6), LAVA (7), ACID (8)\n- GAS: STEAM (12), SMOKE (13), FIRE (14)\n- STATIC: STONE (1), WOOD (9), METAL (10), ICE (11)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Strain-Rate Tensor Computation (Step1)**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step1.cu` (lines 1-181)\n\nStep1 computes the **symmetric strain-rate tensor** D (6 components) for GRANULAR particles:\n\n```cuda\n// D_ab = 0.5 * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (dv_a * gradW_b + dv_b * gradW_a)\nDxx += weight * dvx * gWx;\nDyy += weight * dvy * gWy;\nDzz += weight * dvz * gWz;\nDxy += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWy + dvy * gWx);\nDxz += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWz + dvz * gWx);\nDyz += 0.5f * weight * (dvy * gWz + dvz * gWy);\n\n// PostCalc: gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D)\nfloat D_sq = Dxx*Dxx + Dyy*Dyy + Dzz*Dzz + 2.0f*(Dxy*Dxy + Dxz*Dxz + Dyz*Dyz);\nfloat gamma_dot = sqrt(2.0f * D_sq);\nshear_rate_out[index_i] = gamma_dot;  // For non-GRANULAR, write 0\n```\n\n**Data Pipeline:**\n- Step1 outputs: `shear_rate` (gamma_dot per particle)\n- Reorder kernel sorts this into `sorted_shear_rate`\n- Step2 kernel reads from Step1's neighbor pass (not from sorted array — computed inline)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Constant Memory Layout**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` (lines 69-128)\n\n```cuda\n__constant__ MaterialProps c_materials[32];           // 32*64 = 2048 bytes\n__constant__ Interaction   c_interactions[32][32];    // 32*32*8 = 8192 bytes\n__constant__ GridParams    c_grid;                    // ~60 bytes\n__constant__ SimParams     c_sim;                     // ~60 bytes\n__constant__ PrecalcParams c_precalc;                 // 20 bytes\n```\n\n**Additional Step2 constant memory:**\n```cuda\n__constant__ GranularParams c_granular;               // 32 bytes (local to step2.cu)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Key mu(I) Formulas (Implemented in Step2)**\n\nFrom lines 13-16 of step2.cu header and lines 122-129:\n\n1. **Inertial number**: `I = gamma_dot * d / sqrt(p_eff / rho)`\n   - `d = particle_spacing = 0.02`\n   - `p_eff = max(p, 1.0)` — clamp to prevent division by zero\n\n2. **Friction coefficient**: `mu(I) = mu_s + (mu_2 - mu_s) / (1 + I0 / max(I, 1e-8))`\n   - Transitions from `mu_s=0.36` (static) to `mu_2=0.70` (dynamic)\n   - Reference inertial number `I0=0.3`\n\n3. **Dynamic viscosity**: `eta_i = min(mu_max, mu0 + mu(I) * p_eff / (gamma_dot + 1e-6))`\n   - Base viscosity `mu0 = 3.5` Pa*s\n   - Maximum cap `mu_max = 10000` Pa*s (critical to prevent infinities)\n\n4. **Harmonic mean for pair viscosity**:\n   ```cuda\n   eta_ij = 2.0f * eta_i * eta_j / (eta_i + eta_j + 1e-8f)\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Python API for Parameter Upload**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/step2.py` (lines 84-191)\n\n```python\ndef build_granular_params(\n    mu_s=0.36, mu_2=0.70, I0=0.3, mu_max=10000.0,\n    particle_spacing=0.02, mu0=3.5, xsph_epsilon=0.5\n) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"Build GranularParams struct as numpy structured array.\"\"\"\n    params = np.zeros(1, dtype=GRANULAR_PARAMS_DTYPE)\n    params[0][\"mu_s\"] = mu_s\n    params[0][\"mu_2\"] = mu_2\n    params[0][\"I0\"] = I0\n    params[0][\"mu_max\"] = mu_max\n    params[0][\"particle_spacing\"] = particle_spacing\n    params[0][\"mu0\"] = mu0\n    params[0][\"xsph_epsilon\"] = xsph_epsilon\n    return params\n\ndef upload_granular_params(params: Optional[np.ndarray] = None) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Upload GranularParams to __constant__ GranularParams c_granular.\"\"\"\n    if params is None:\n        params = build_granular_params()\n    module = _get_module()\n    d_ptr = module.get_global(\"c_granular\")\n    cupy.cuda.runtime.memcpy(int(d_ptr), params.ctypes.data, params.nbytes, 1)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **File Organization Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Content |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `step2.cu` | Main Step2 kernel | mu(I) rheology, pressure, viscosity, XSPH |\n| `step1.cu` | Density + strain-rate | Symmetric tensor D computation, gamma_dot output |\n| `common.cuh` | Shared constants | BehaviorClass, MaterialProps, GridParams, SimParams, PrecalcParams |\n| `step2.py` | Python wrapper | GranularParams struct, kernel launch, constant memory upload |\n| `step1.py` | Python wrapper | Step1 launch, shear_rate output handling |\n| `materials.py` | Material definitions | 16 materials with behavior classes, EOS properties, color |\n| `simulation.py` | Main loop | Orchestrates Step1 → Reorder → Step2 → Integrate |\n\n---\n\n### 10. **mu(I) Usage by Behavior Class**\n\n- **GRANULAR**: Full mu(I) viscosity with harmonic mean for GRANULAR-GRANULAR pairs\n- **FLUID/GAS**: Constant viscosity (`mu0 * 45/(pi*h^6)`) — mu(I) not applied\n- **STATIC**: Skipped entirely (zero force output)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Test Coverage**\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_step1.py` (lines 467-622)\n\nStrain-rate tests:\n- `test_stationary_sand_zero_gamma_dot()` — gamma_dot ~ 0 for stationary particles\n- `test_shear_flow_nonzero_gamma_dot()` — gamma_dot > 0 in velocity gradient\n- `test_non_granular_zero_shear_rate()` — FLUID particles always get shear_rate = 0\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Current Implementation Status**\n\nPer the PRD (`fallingsand3d/prd.json`):\n- **US-015** (COMPLETED): Strain-rate tensor in Step1 ✓\n- **US-016** (IN PROGRESS): mu(I) viscosity in Step2 ✓\n- **US-017**: Velocity clamp for granular (pending)\n- **US-023**: Adaptive timestep with CFL constraints (requires mu_max awareness)\n\nAll mu(I) parameters are now **hardcoded as defaults** in `step2.py` and uploadable via `upload_granular_params()`.\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete mu(I) rheology implementation. The system is fully functional for GRANULAR materials with dynamic friction, inertial number scaling, and viscosity clamping. Let me know if you need deeper analysis of any specific component!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5771fa (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 85783\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 46663</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b25de12-98cf-4fd9-9de1-d55f6bd80115","uuid":"c5f213e3-f260-47ed-8850-fe61a4ece5c9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current state of the Step2 kernel and any mu(I) rheology implementation. Please search the codebase thoroughly for:\n\n1. The Step2 kernel implementation - find the main kernel file (likely in fallingsand3d/ directory, a .cu or .py file)\n2. Any existing mu(I) references (mu_s, mu_2, I0, mu_max, gamma_dot, strain rate, eta_ij, harmonic mean)\n3. The common.cuh or sim params file where constants are defined\n4. The behavior class definitions (GRANULAR, FLUID, GAS)\n5. Any existing viscosity force computation in Step2\n\nSearch in /c/WORK/gpusphsim/ recursively. Show me the relevant file paths and key code sections.","agentId":"a5771fa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: Step2 Kernel & mu(I) Rheology Implementation\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the `/c/WORK/gpusphsim` co